{#==============================================================================
  complex_lease.j2  —  High structural-density residential lease
==============================================================================#}
<h1 class="doc-title">RESIDENTIAL LEASE AGREEMENT</h1>

<p class="meta-line">
  This Agreement is made on {{ meta.agreement_date }} and governed by the laws of
  {{ meta.jurisdiction }}.
</p>

<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">1.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">PARTIES.</span>
</p>
<p class="sub-clause">
  <span class="clause-num">1.1</span>
  Landlord: {{ landlord.name }}, mailing address {{ landlord.address }}.
</p>
<p class="sub-clause">
  <span class="clause-num">1.2</span>
  Tenant(s): {{ tenants | map(attribute='name') | join('; ') }}.
  Each individual named as a Tenant is jointly and severally liable for all
  obligations under this Agreement.
</p>

<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">2.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">PREMISES.</span>
</p>
<p class="sub-clause">
  <span class="clause-num">2.1</span>
  Address: {{ property.address }}.
</p>
<p class="sub-clause">
  <span class="clause-num">2.2</span>
  Legal description: {{ property.legal_description }}.
</p>
<p class="sub-clause">
  <span class="clause-num">2.3</span>
  Residence type: {{ property.type }}. The foregoing is the "Premises".
</p>

<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">3.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">TERM.</span>
</p>
<p class="sub-clause">
  <span class="clause-num">3.1</span>
  Commencement: {{ term.start }}. Expiration: {{ term.end }}.
</p>
<p class="sub-clause">
  <span class="clause-num">3.2</span>
  Renewal: Upon expiration and absent renewal, the Tenant
{%- if term.renewal == 'month_to_month' %}
  may continue on a month-to-month basis terminable on {{ term.notice_days }}
  days' written notice by either Party.
{%- else %}
  must vacate the Premises.
{%- endif %}
</p>

<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">4.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">DEFINITIONS.</span>
  The following terms have the meanings assigned below and are
  capitalized throughout this Agreement:
</p>
<p class="sub-clause">
  <span class="clause-num">4.1</span>
  "Rent" means the monthly sum payable under Section 5.
</p>
<p class="sub-clause">
  <span class="clause-num">4.2</span>
  "Security Deposit" means the sum held under Section 7 as security for the
  Tenant's performance.
</p>
<p class="sub-clause">
  <span class="clause-num">4.3</span>
  "Due Date" means the {{ rent.due_day }} day of each calendar month.
</p>
<p class="sub-clause">
  <span class="clause-num">4.4</span>
  "Default" has the meaning assigned in Section 10.
</p>

<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">5.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">RENT.</span>
  The Tenant shall pay Rent of ${{ "%.2f" | format(rent.amount) }} per
  month, payable in advance on each Due Date (as defined in Section 4.3).
</p>

<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">6.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">LATE CHARGE.</span>
  If Rent is not received within {{ late_fee.grace_days }} day(s)
  after the Due Date, the Tenant shall pay a late charge of
  ${{ "%.2f" | format(late_fee.amount) }}. Assessment of late charges is subject
  to {{ meta.late_fee_statute }}.
</p>

<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">7.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">SECURITY DEPOSIT.</span>
</p>
<p class="sub-clause">
  <span class="clause-num">7.1</span>
  Amount: ${{ "%.2f" | format(deposit.amount) }}, due on execution.
</p>
<p class="sub-clause">
  <span class="clause-num">7.2</span>
  Return: The Security Deposit (as defined in Section 4.2), less itemized
  deductions, shall be returned within {{ deposit.return_days }} days after
  surrender, in accordance with {{ meta.deposit_statute }}.
</p>
<p class="sub-clause">
  <span class="clause-num">7.3</span>
  The Security Deposit shall not be applied to Rent (Section 5) without the
  Landlord's written consent.
</p>

{% if not edges.omit_pet_section -%}
<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">8.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">PETS.</span>
{%- if pets.allowed %}
  The Tenant may keep pets not exceeding {{ pets.max_weight }} lbs, subject to a
  fee of ${{ "%.2f" | format(pets.fee) }}. The Tenant is liable for all
  pet-related damage and shall restore the Premises at the Tenant's expense.
{%- else %}
  No pets are permitted on the Premises or in common areas.
{%- endif %}
</p>
{%- else -%}
<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">8.</span>
  <span class="clause-title reserved">[RESERVED]</span>
</p>
{%- endif %}

<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">9.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">RIGHT OF ENTRY.</span>
  The Landlord may enter the Premises upon at least 24 hours'
  written notice for inspection, repairs, or showings, except that no notice is
  required in an emergency.
</p>

<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">10.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">DEFAULT.</span>
  The Tenant is in Default if the Tenant (a) fails to pay Rent or other
  amounts when due; (b) violates any term of this Agreement; or (c) abandons the
  Premises. Upon Default the Landlord may exercise all remedies available under
  this Agreement and applicable law.
</p>

<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">11.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">SUBLETTING.</span>
{%- if sublet.allowed %}
{%- if edges.cross_ref_sublet %}
  The Tenant may sublet only with the Landlord's prior written consent. Consent
  to one subtenant does not constitute consent to any subsequent subtenant, and
  a subletting Tenant remains liable under Section 1.2 (joint and several
  liability) and is not released from the obligations defined in Section 10.
{%- else %}
  The Tenant may sublet only with the Landlord's prior written consent.
{%- endif %}
{%- else %}
  The Tenant may not sublet the Premises.
{%- endif %}
</p>

<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">12.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">MAINTENANCE.</span>
  The Tenant shall maintain the Premises in clean and sanitary
  condition and surrender it as received, normal wear and tear excepted.
</p>

<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">13.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">SMOKE ALARMS &amp; SECURITY DEVICES.</span>
  The Premises is equipped with smoke alarms
  and exterior-door security devices as required by applicable law. Requests for
  repair must be in writing.
</p>

{% if edges.conflicting_late_fee -%}
<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">14.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">ADDITIONAL FEE PROVISIONS.</span>
  Notwithstanding any other provision, a late charge of
  ${{ "%.2f" | format(late_fee_conflict_amount) }} shall apply to any Rent paid
  after the Due Date.
</p>
{%- else -%}
<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">14.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">SEVERABILITY.</span>
  If any provision of this Agreement is held unenforceable, the
  remainder shall remain in full force and effect.
</p>
{%- endif %}

<p class="clause">
  <span class="clause-num">15.</span>
  <span class="clause-title">ENTIRE AGREEMENT.</span>
  This Agreement, together with any addenda, constitutes the
  entire agreement between the Parties and supersedes all prior negotiations,
  understandings, and oral agreements.
</p>

<div class="signatures">
  <div class="section-heading">SIGNATURES</div>

  <div class="sig-block">
    <div class="sig-line">Landlord: _________________________&nbsp;&nbsp;Date: __________</div>
    <div class="sig-name">{{ landlord.name }}</div>
  </div>

{% for t in tenants -%}
  <div class="sig-block">
    <div class="sig-line">Tenant: ___________________________&nbsp;&nbsp;Date: __________</div>
    <div class="sig-name">{{ t.name }}</div>
  </div>
{% endfor -%}
</div>
